caption: It was hard to find a place to eat that offered outdoor dining tonight. My friends and I came into Benchmark for a quick eat and some wine. We got to sit on their outdoor patio area which was away from the tent they had but was still safe and adherent to covid protocols. We had appetizers and drinks and our server Jason was very courteous and friendly. Nice atmosphere and the food was delicious! Thank you Benchmark for the excellent experience! We will be back!

Wonderful staff and great food. The veal chop Wellington was ridiculously huge and tasty. The fried chocolate chip cookie dough egg roll is a fantastic end to a sumptuous dinner. They offer inside and outdoor seating.   Can't wait to return.

This is nice cozy spot, that I booked at the very last minute without any prior knowledge.  The experience wasn't disappointed me at all. Very quiet and nice place with very pleasant stuff. The food was interesting and tasty.  I wasn't really hungry,  so I wouldn't try too many things,  so I will definitely come back for more.

Went there around 12.30 for brunch. It was easy to find meter parking around. Was a bit nervous about how outdoor seating would be, to our surprise it was relatively cozy while it was 30F. We ordered chicken wings for apps and it was delicious! The benchmark burger was decent, I think the blue cheese was a bit over powering, however, the fries were amazing. The staff was extremely attentive and super friendly, I will definitely be coming back!
This restaurant gives awesome service and yummy meals. One of the best spot ever. The meals served quick and the rates were inexpensive. Highly recommended.
Nice staff, amazing food!!!
Ouside in open tent, but warm.Amped up menu. Vt skilodge theme.
Awesome food and drinks with great outside heating....you will definitely enjoy dinner here!
Nice place for a casual or friendly dinner.

Best steaks in The Slope! My bestie and I came in for a quick bite to get out of the wind & cold. Benchmark has a nice semi-covered patio with heat! Hard to find off 5th Ave! Their Hottie cocktails are SUPERB! Our server was terrific and the steaks and fries were delicious! The cookie dough egg roll dessert is so tasty. We will be back! :)

We met with friends at this spot for a meeting. my friend recommended this restaurant.  Well, it was very successful. The staff were extremely nice and we felt fantastic. The meal was yummy. We had a great time and we shall definitely come back again. Recommended.
Good food is hard to find
Large outdoor space and excellent food, paired with friendly service.
Wowww this was good. Delicious steak, tons of great appetizers, and the cookie dough egg roll dessert was phenomenal. Great outdoor setup, too!
Great brunch! Outdoor seating was great, food was delicious, safely spaced, super clean. Service was excellent, friendly and helpful.

My bestie and I came for dinner on Friday. Restaurant was busy and lively with a wedding party. We were sat promptly and we were served immediately. Food is AMAZING! Cocktails were boozy and our waiter Jason was exceptional. We never had to wait for drinks, appetizers and finally our dinner. Their outdoor dining setup is cozy and inviting. We will definitely be back. Thank you Jason for the great experience!:)
Always great food and great service!

This place was excellent. One of the few places in park slope with outdoor seating that isn't right on the street. All the food was excellent. Spanish twist on a steakhouse, with italian influence? Whatever you classify this place as, it's unique and memorable

Always excellent food, atmosphere, and service. Just came here during the pandemic and the spacing between tables and safety precautions are amazing and you will feel very safe. Have always loved their brunch food and the steaks are always amazing. Would recommend to anyone.
Delicious! A special place for our family  celebrating milestones. Today my sons 21st birthday. He loved his steak!!
Great service, terrific food. Our special occasion place.
Some of the best foie gras outside of France. All the appetizers are amazing - stick to those and the desert. #vero #travel #brooklyn

I'd eaten at Benchmark before the shutdown  and always enjoyed the food, drink and atmosphere. When we walked by and saw it was open, we stopped in for a drink (always delicious) and picked out a couple of appetizers...pretty. much as a second thought. We had nachos and fries with no expectations. What a surprise. The nachos were unusually prepared and very tasty and satisfying (not the gooey mess I had anticipated). The fries were as they should be,  hand cut, crispy outside with a tender center. Yum. Plan to go back for a real dinner soon. The other attraction is that they have outdoor seating, with distance spacing, in their front courtyard. The feeling is more like being in a restaurant than eating on the street. Enjoy!
Amazing cookie dough egg roll!!
Really nice spot for outdoor dining.
Bartender is the best and is super friendly
Excellent food
This place offers wonderful service as well as enjoyable menu. One of my favourite spots in the area. The meals served quick and the prices are affordable. Will definitely recommend this spot.
For the price absolutely the best steak in south Brooklyn. Not to mention their menu is revolutionary while being classic!
A gem!

This place is a solid brunch spot (probably 3-4 stars for brunch), but severely disappointing for dinner. Especially for a special dinner. Their Valentine’s Day prefixed menu was over priced and severely underwhelming. My partner and I came in with high hopes after positive brunch experiences here, but the food was bland at best and over-cooked at worst. Dry fish, overcooked pork, over frozen ice cream...just to name a few. What a terrible disappointment for $95/person. Don’t waste your money, come here for brunch only.
Good food and service
Love this place!
Excellent wine list and always a great steak.
Went there for a friends wedding reception, was a great time despite being set outside under a mock extension of the restaurant.  Drinks were great too would go back again

Came in for a steak after visiting my son before he had to return to West Point. Benchmark Restaurant is Park Slope’s hidden gem. Sat at the bar as to not take up a perfectly good table just for myself. Jason was exceptional in his service, conversation and tending to whatever I needed. Cocktails and wines are outstanding. Will definitely be back when I come for another visit. A+ experience.

Interesting layout for a restaurant, garden area is covered in a tent for the winter and seems like it would be nice in the summer.  Food was mostly great. Fantastic burger, really well cooked and seasoned. Great bacon.
Absolutely fabulous.  Food AND service exceptional 💖

First want to say the food was pretty delicious but the drinks were sub par snd the customer service was awful! We called to say we were a few minutes late for our reservation but were right around the corner and they said it was no issue. When we arrived we were asked to wait for a minute so we waited by the door which was right next to an open table. After about 5 minutes a waitress came up and said "oh, you can just sit at that table" (the same one that had been open since we walked in) The waitress ended up being helpful with wine choices but was very passive aggressive at every interaction. Do not recommend wasting your time or money here when there are so many other houses that have the same or better quality food along with acceptable service.
Unfriendly
Good food, great service, good brunch options, and if it's your birthday, fun dessert.
Food is great.

Had a delicious soup that I wanted to mop up with some of their soft bread but a server cleared my plate before I had a chance. I wouldn't recommend sitting in the heated tent outside. Not sure if one of the heaters shut off during my meal but I was freezing before the end of the main course. The temperature also turned my fries ice cold in an instant. Altogether, didn't expect much and didn't get much
The service is always excellent at this local spot. They have an extensive wine list and delectable steak and salad.

A perfect spot for brunch in Brooklyn. They have both indoor and outdoor seating. Good service and tasty food. For three people we paid just over $60 (two omelettes, one lobster roll, one side pancake, and coffee). We got there at 11 on Sunday and there were plenty of tables available, but around noon, it got more crowded. BTW, on-street parking only.
Grrat service. Quality meat.

Favorite place ever! Their staff, food, service, atmosphere, and their drinks are hands down just out of this world! My husband and I live in NJ now but we always come here when we are in town. Highly recommend definitely deserve beyond 5 star rating!

The food was savory, flavorful, and filling. The service was impeccable and friendly. Would recommend as a great dinner date spot or friendly group meal. The price is on the spot for the high quality of the meal.

The best food, best service, great outdoor back alley seating. Cocktails great too. Menu is a little short but if you like steak there's plenty of options. If not they have a very nice squash entree. An urban oasis
Beautiful atmosphere, delicious starters and great service
(Translated by Google) I went to the $ 43 event and it's not very good. Go somewhere else  (Original) 43달러 이벤트해서 갔는데 너무 별로에요. 다른데 가시길
Great ambiance, food, and service. Excellent wine list. What more do I want?
Delicious food, hidden location, good waiters will definitely return.

Not my favorite burger in the neighborhood (I prefer Blue Ribbon), but Benchmark has a nice ambiance (in an old carriage house with a big outdoor space in the front) and is about as close to a fancy steakhouse as we have in Park Slope (with a price tag to match).
Amazing food, service and the ambience is to die for.
Some Steakhouses in this part of Bklyn!

During Restaurant Week (7/22/2019) I came to enjoy a 3 course dinner at Benchmark and it was DEEELLLLIIICCCCIIIIOOOOUUUUSSSSS!!!! From my appetizer (steak and tomato salad), my entree (Mahi mahi), and cookie dough egg roll, I enjoyed every bite. An added bonus, I went on a Monday and it was half price on bottled wine! Enjoyed a bottle of Petite Sirah. Definitely recommend this restaurant to friends, family, or a solo outing like I had.
Food was amazing ,,,,,,,,,,nice place
Good was fresh and delicious. Many many options. Big portions. Great service. Our new fave restarant in the slope.
Top notch staff and environment I have experienced in a extremely long time

Very friendly staff. The food is amazing. They are very accommodating. We got there early and the staff was able to make an early accommodating for us while we were waiting for the rest of the party to arrive. Definitely he order their pancakes. It's very decadent. There omelette was very good and came with wheat toast and you can add a side order of the marinated salmon. Overall, this is a very comfortable place for a family gathering
Best lunch we had in our whole week in NY. Service was great and food was amazing! If you're vegetarian or not, you'll find what suits you !

(Translated by Google) A terrace set back to enjoy the evening a drink in hand before a delicious meal. It is on the meat that this restaurant scores its points in gold. A fine wine list with a wide choice of countries of origin allows to harmonize its choices with the dishes. The range of homemade desserts can close in beauty. I recommend.  (Original) Une terrasse en retrait pour profiter du soir un verre à la main avant un délicieux repas. C est sur la viande que ce restaurant marque ses points en or. Une belle carte des vins avec un large choix de pays d d'origine permet d harmoniser ses choix avec les plats. La gamme de desserts maisons permet de clore en beauté.  Je recommande.

Benchmark is a place if I could frequent more would be a good place to be. Steaks are a thing here and the chef knows their thing as they were not to disappoint says cave man me. Staff was amazing and have you bounce back in no time
The steak is to die for

Scallops are amazing, mashed potatoes are amazing and their American kobe is amazing.Girlfriend and I had a great dinner and experience.Jason gave us a round of drinks on him.Thank you.Super nice.We will be coming back shortly.A++ burger joint.
Very bad service
Ok !!

Great dinner experience! Excellent food & cocktails. Couldn't get seating at a table inside so we rocked it at the bar. Jason always made sure that we had what we needed and was very attentive. Had some George Harrison playing on the speakers! Nice environment and their wine list is exceptional.
Been here many times. After tonight not sure if I come back. Literally everything way too salty
Very nice brunch ! Great service. Steak and eggs were great and nice portions. Spinach/blueberry salad plus three egg omelette was a  tasty lunch.
Excellent. Good friendly service
Food and service were both excellent! Cozy atmosphere and decent prices. Highly recommended!
Food was delicious!!

The atmosphere was very cozy, elegant and yet comfortable.  The food was delicious!! This was my third visit.  This is a steakhouse (no chicken!!).  I had the burger this time and they did not fail me!! It was superb...will be going back again and again.

Came here for NYC Restaurant Week. The food was incredible, best steak I've had in a long while, cooked to perfection. The cookie dough eggrolls were amazing! Extensive wine list... we ended up with a nice Sancerre. Service was great... Very friendly and happy to offer suggestions. Definitely coming back again!

I came for Restaurant week. It was an awesome experience. The filet mignon was well cooked and paired perfectly with the mashed potatoes and vegetables. The bread pudding with bourbon gelato was also delicious.

I had a great time going to benchmark for brunch. We sat at the bar, and were attended by a wonderful bartender. The food was southern style and delicious, I particularly recommend the strawberry shortcake donut holes. I've never had anything like them, and they were quite tasty.
It's a relaxed atmosphere and the music in the background  would even make goldilocks happy, just right! Lol.

I only had dessert but the strawberry shortcake was delicious and the extra spicy Bloody Mary was perfection. In addition our group was left alone to chat and no one rushed us which I was thoroughly grateful for!
Fantastic food! A friend and I had dinner here and it was just great. Prices seem more than fair for the quality of food too. We'll definitely come back!
Pretty nice place
Great food and service
I went here for Thanksgiving, it was a nice small intimate spot. Lots of potential in the summer time due to the out door seating area. The ambiance and food was good.
You can never go wrong with the cookie dough egg roll

We had a fantastic steak dinner with our daughter while celebrating three days of being 100% NYC tourists for a few days. We are from the Midwest and are accustomed to high-quality beef. We were totally awed by the perfect flavor, preparation, and presentation. Our server was so personable and fun! We hope to visit again. Thanks for a great wrap up  for our amazing trip!

5 star experience. Had Thanksgiving dinner with my parents. Food and menu was delicious. The service is first rate. Our waitress was bubbly. Chef is top tier. Drinks very satisfying. My father had the Up n Smoke and passed it around.Was taken back by the array of flavors and taste.  Mezcal was very tasty. Jason, very friendly, walked us through the process of the ingredients and how the drink is made. Great experience and recommend to all passing through Park Slope. Thank you Sofie.
Great dining experience every time I visit.
Great food and service! Thank you!

Had amazing chilaquiles for brunch a few weekends ago. The restaurant is housed in an old carriage house behind a courtyard and contains retro land surveying equipment found when excavating the property (hence benchmark). The music was great and the server was welcoming and attentive. Definitely will be back.
Nice brunch
I cannot recommend this restaurant highly enough! Great service with perfect melt in your mouth steak that didn't break the bank accompanied by wonderful wine.
Great food
Great ambiance and delicious food!
The food was amazing!!
Nice place to eat
Great Resturant! Great Prices
food is Excellent
Nice place actually really nice place
Good food.  Great service.  Nice laid back vibe.
Lots of great food and nice staff
Great brunch spot in beautiful Park Slope.
Absolutely amazing food everytime. The best steaks I've ever had!
Great brunch.
Great food, excellent presentation.
One of our favorite local places for brunch and dinner. The seared fois gras is out of this world and the menu has something for every taste.  They make a wicked good Bloody Mary as well.

Went for restaurant week so it was a bit busy and the wait was long but it's restaurant week. That's to be expected. The waiter was courteous and knowledgeable about wine selection and pairing compared to a novice like me. They have a nice selection of scotch, I had the highland park. I had the ribeye which was fantastic. It comes with a selection of sauces but it doesn't even need it. Superb on its own. The foie gras melted in your mouth and dessert was exceptional. Definitely a date night kind of place.

Went for a quiet date night and had a great time. The servers were all extremely friendly, going out of their way to make everything convenient for us. For example, I was struggling a bit to find the entrance because it’s set back from the street, and the host jogged after me to show me in. It was raining and I was wet and they offered me towels. The food was also great. I had the restaurant week menu of peach burrata (perfect and fresh), pasta, and the cookie dough egg roll. We also tried the Brussel sprouts and seasonal lettuces. I can’t remember the name of the cocktail I got but it was perfect. I’d say expect to spent about $30-40 a head. I would definitely go again.

Service was good and the atmosphere is nice, but all the food we ordered was extremely bland with no flavor at all. Between the tuna, porterhouse and salmon you'd think one would be good, but we left very disappointed.

Without a doubt one of the best restaurants in New York City. I recently had the reception for my wedding here and the food and service were exemplary. Order the Filet Mignon or Ribeye when you're here and you won't be disappointed.
The place is awesome it's has great music and everything!The only thing that I think they should improve their French toast.Without that it awesome!WOOHOOOO!
Excellent steak house. Get the steak with a side fantastic. Good service
Great afternoon lunch with my girlfriends. Food was tasty, wine was good (a little overpriced) yet delicious. Waiter was awesome!
From Restaurant Week - Dinner
Nice place.
Go to place for a steak and eggs brunch in Brooklyn. Nuff said!

After spending almost a week in Brooklyn for our daughter's wedding, my wife and I came across Benchmark while we were out trying to unwind and just take a break from the hustle of the week's activities. If you ever come to Park Slope, don't blink, you might miss where it is tucked away! The location is great. The outdoor dining area feels so relaxing. There is no music just the sounds of the day. Whether that is by choice or because of the close proximity of houses nearby, it was a nice atmosphere to start. The weather was just a bit to hot for us so we asked if we could move inside which our server was more than happy to do. Once inside the restaurant you automatically feel relaxed. The lighting levels were perfect and they had music playing from my generation so I felt at ease! We did not know that it was restaurant week when we arrived so we had to wait at the bar for a table to clear. My wife and I did not have to wait to be greeted by the bartender who, without asking, brought us chilled glasses of water. The service here is exceptional. Jason (the bartender) was very professional and kind in allowing us the time to preview over their drink menu. I am a Gin aficionado...long story short I had the best (10 stars) Gin martini that I have had in a while. My wife had a glass of wine and we were set. Once seated, Nathan our server treated us like we were the only two in the restaurant. Sea scallops are out of this world delicious; the lobster bisque = amazing and their signature benchmark burgers are the top of the line.  Thank you benchmark for helping us relax and enjoy our last dining out in Brooklyn! We will be back.

Words cannot describe how amazing this meal was. Went here for restaurant week and I have 0 complaints. Nice, quiet place, with a small garden to take photos in. Our server was so happy and attentive. He recommended a wonderful sparkling red for dinner and then we enjoyed drink at the bar that was as interesting as it was tasty.

Great waitstaff, super attentive. Not too much is offered on the menu, but just enough. Perfect for an indecisive person like me. Perfect place whether you want to eat in or out.  Get the scallops, you’ll thank me later.

Went here with my wife.  We normally don't do brunch, but because we've heard good things about this place, we gave it a shot.  Holy cow.  We had the donut holes which were absolutely amazing.  Wife had lemon and ricotta pancakes and I had the steak and eggs.  Our plates were truly delicious, and the wait time for them was not too bad.  Dessert was the cookie dough eggroll, and despite the weird name, it was delicious.  Also, their bacon...it may have been  some of the best bacon I've had.  When there was one last piece, the wife and I were both eyeing before deciding to be civil and share.  This place snuck up on us.  We knew were going to get good food, but this was lip smacking, eye rolling, I-may-want-my-last-meal-here-before-i-die good.  Our server was awesome too.  Calm, cool, collected - he knew when to come to us without making us feel rushed.  Oh, and a bit of good natured warning - their Benchmark Bloody Mary was STRONG.  I don't mean that in a bad way either - it made for an damn good drink, and you know they weren't stingy with the booze.  All in all  it really was a great experience and pleasure to go there again.  This place may not be affordable enough to go there once a week, but you're absolutley, without a doubt, getting every penny you spend there.

Ate here yesterday. Scallops were past their prime. I ordered the tuna with pickled chantrelles, but it came with soggy portabella mushrooms when it arrived at the table. I don't know if they just forgot the change the menu or if they really thought no one would notice the difference between saffron yellow chantrelles mushrooms and grey/brown portabella mushrooms, but that pissed me off.  Service was fine, atmosphere was fine.
Quality restaurant Local.  Nice and respectful service
Delicious
(Translated by Google) Great. The meat was perfect.  (Original) Excelente. A carne estava perfeita.
The steaks here are quite special and the brunch cupcakes are killer! Servers are always super kind, definitely a great brooklyn gem!
Good service, nice steaks.
Great place
Solid local brunch location. outside is nice in the right conditions but lacks any breeze when too hot

After ordering five different items including dinners and openings from the menu, each item was prepared perfectly deliciously and then artistically plated. Special shout-out to the duck salad and stuffed squash items.  Make sure to check your receipt as the bill presented was off by $900.00 lol. A $9 beverage was overcharged but when pointed out, the drink was given free and the bill was changed to reflect the correct amount. All in all we were very happy with the service we received and all our food choices.

This place should have a Michelin star...it's that good. The dishes are inventive and the chef gives each dish a little native flare...for example their spicy lobster salad with banana guacamole...all I can say is, wow! Their tuna dish is another rockstar in their arsenal of flavor....and can we talk about the desserts? Insanely good, Jo matter what you have!  Now, let's talk about the service... extremely attentive and not at all intrusive...the bus boy, was on top of our beverage needs the entire time, and not once did I have to search for our waitress or our bus boy on the floor, they worked like poetry in motion, and it was actually a pleasure to see them work together.  Now let's talk about the ambiance - first class...whether you're sitting outside in the garden or dining inside (I recommend inside) only because it feels a little like a naughty speakeasy...it's warm, inviting and the seating is oh so comfortable. I can not wait to go back!

Service was excellent however food was waaaaaaaay overpriced, not hot, and special pasta was horrible. They butterflied an expensive filet mignon and crab pasta was like eating cold broken up tuna. Overall disappointing. I would only go back for drinks.

Third time to Benchmark and each time the food and experience gets better. Had the swordfish special that came with an unexpectedly perfect pesto and vegetable medley. Also, our waitress recommended a seriously bold Syrah that went perfect with my meal and my friend's rib eye (which I have also eaten. It's a sizable cut that's cooked and seasoned like a big named steakhouse). Highly recommended!
Really great atmosphere, service and most importantly, the food!
Been here twice now for brunch and both times the food has been pretty bland and mediocre. Service, atmosphere, and drinks are good though.

Benchmark is Park Slope's best kept restuarant secret! The moment you walk into the restaurant you feel cozy and relaxed. After running around Manhattan all day, it was nice to walk in and be greeted with a smile and sat quickly. Our waiter Tony was friendly and always made sure we had want we wanted and needed. Their menu is great and their cocktails were amazing! My friends and I had the house 'Southern Punch' which was so delicious! We couldn't have just one! Jason the bartender was friendly and quick in getting our drinks made for us. All in all, it was a great dinner and a great night for my girlfriends and I. We will defintely be back again!
The food and the service are amazing!
Good but not great food. It is very, very noisy. No easy parking. Perhaps not worth it.
I had a burger and some fries. It was great
Has a very intimate and cozy aura about this place. And I love it.
Delicious hamburger and some of the best fries I have ever had!

Horrable service, owner didnt want to comout and appologize or even talk to us. Instead sent his girl who gave a hole speech of how he is busy at the kitchen, they have sprcific alcohol rules, if your bottle is 10 times more expensive then whst they have on shelve they will give you a while speech about licensing and etc (which doesnt exist). But loom at the picture, since "they are so much into law, they have no problem underage kid sitting at the bar table. Highly do not recomend
Best steakhouse and brunch in BK
Great atmosphere,delicious food and wonderful service!
This was my first visit to Benchmark. My girlfriend took me there. The experience was great. Food was delicious, staff was friendly and place was nice and cozy.
Friendly staffs and nice quality food. Steak is nicer than fish dishes. Nice price point for the food quality and portion.
The steak and cookie dough spring roll’s were amazing. The service was good, but not excellent. The scallops were great, but there were only three of them.
There’s better restaurants it wasn’t all that.

Amazing steak, fish, and more. The food here is truly reflective of the restaurant name. I have been here multiple times over the course of many years and the quality of the food and service has always been excellent. Good cocktails and wine list never hurts either!
AMAZING!!!
Good food. Great interior.  Small establishment but limited staffing. Server is the host, runner and bartender hence an extra wait.

Came for a friends 60th birthday overall the service was good and the food was good. Steak was nice and juicy and wasn't super expensive. The biggest disappointment was the cookie dough egg roll. The shell was def too hot for the cookie dough to be piped in and made it melt. The cookie dough wasn't very good either.

The place its self is nice to look at but the food had little flavor. Seemed as if the chef didn't know how to use salt or any other spices to spice up what I thought should have been an easy brunch plan.
Wonderful spot great food prices really reasonable

Always love the food and drink. Waiter today seemed a little 🙄 Zombie-esque. Maybe Sunday brunch drained him by the time we got there? On the flip side, one of the waitresses has a great Amy Schumer kind of personality and jokes. Never overcrowded, just enough buzz. Good place to go with a group or just one.

Had the ribeye and filet mignon. They were cooked perfectly. We had the cheese platter appetizer which had large pieces of cheese we wouldn't see at other restaurants. We had sides of fries, Mac and cheese, and the brussel sprouts... All of which were to die for. We finished our meal with the strawberry shortcake and there couldn't have been a better way to end the meal. I highly recommend this restaurant!
I know steak. Their dry aged New York strip was perfect. Side were very very good.  Wine list extensive.
cozy decor, nice location, however the filet mignon and ribeye we had were below standard.
It was a real pleasure to have a lunch in the Benchmark. We wanted a good meat and we found it! It was excellent see the pictures =)
The cookie dough egg rolls are delicious.
Amazing food, ambience and service.

Place was very nice and elegant reminded me of over seas restaurant. Great music (Jazz, modern music with a twist.) Reason I gave it a three stars was due to the food. The menu selection was kinda small in my opinion  and I eat NOTHING while I was there.But beside that it was fine. I recommend checking menu before going.

This is an elegant, amazing restaurant! Great service, beautiful decor, lovely food. Definitely recommend going there for brunch. Family friendly as well! I've been to a lot of places in Park Slope and only here does it truly feel like not everything is being rushed and they actually care about your experience. 5/5 Muy bien.
Simply delightful, quietly elegant.
Nice quaint restaurant, I love the Arnold Palmer's ice tea, otherwise the portions are small. Great cookies dough desert

Not the same when Ryan isn't there. Meat temperatures vary significantly, makes it very uncomfortable for the service staff to argue with the customers and chef releasing the dishes. 3 out 4 Chocolate 3's came out fully melted. Have been coming for year, never had it this bad.
Fine upscale restaurant casual attire is fine extremely fine food.
Always a great time and meal
Porter house rocked. Cooked perfectly, rare+  Staff worked hard. Good advice on the wine. Would love to go back.
MOSQUITOES, MOSQUITOES, MOSQUITOES!! Invest into some insect control please!!
Spacious outdoor area. Diner-like menu for brunch with sub-par pancakes. Friendly service.
Clean and comfortable.. Most of all the food was tasty..

We went for our dinner and had our 7 year old son with us. We were seated right away and the service was excellent. our waiter Nick was outstanding. He immediately catered to our son. Without asking he told us they have chicken fingers and fries or pasta with butter and cheese for him because it's not on the menu. Our steak and chicken was delicious and was the perfect portion. My husband ordered the bread pudding. Nick brought the bread pudding and a birthday cookie dough spring roll for our son. The cookie dough spring roll was to die for!! Thanks Nick for making our dinner the best dining experience we've had this weekend
Best expierence ever, they are always very friendly and the food is just amazing! .. we come here so much that they know us :P.. i would recommend this place to everyone!
Wonderful rib eye, perfectly cooked, really good service, you will love it...
Delicious food, relaxing surrounding and courteous and knowledgeable servers. A delightful experience.
Best place in Brooklyn! We always come here and the food & service are always fantastic. It's a bit on the pricey side but you can't get better steak elsewhere.

I've been for dinner and loved the steak, but not the sides. Went again for brunch, and had a terrific burger and very good fries. I tasted my friend's pancakes which were also tasty. The only miss was the sausage. The decor is peaceful and brunch wasn't overly busy or noisy on a holiday Monday. Service was attentive but not over the top. Will be back.

Great gem in the neighborhood, the atmosphere is so warm yet modern, loved staff, so friendly, but most of all, food is amazing AND reasonable price.  Friend of mine recommended me to it, she said it is her favorite restaurant now I see why
Great food cozy place
If you are looking to get oysters at the bar as their special, do not bother. They usually don't have it. 4 times out 5 times they do not.
Kitchen and wait staff severely under-resourced - at least for this particular brunch. Waited roughly hour for food after ordering.

This is my absolute favorite restaurant in the neighborhood! The food is always delicious, the cocktails and the wine selection superb and the service excellent. Whether you are a vegetarian or a meat lover there is plenty of yumminess on the menu. My favorite vegetarian dish is the acorn squash and the side of Brussels sprouts. The steak selection is amazing and the mashed potatoes  or the French fries are hard to resist. And the deserts! Crazy good!
A hidden treasure in the heart of Brooklyn. Great food and warm and pleasing waitstaff for an excellent dining experience

2 Stars for the decor,  the waiter,  and the willingness to adjust the bill.  This is a steakhouse.  Cook temperature is the most important thing in a steakhouse.  They missed the mark on a $95 Porter house for 2 (that lacked texture and flavor) and when we sent that steak back,  what replaced it was cooked further under.  I ordered a fois gras appetizer.  Even that got sent back for being under.  This isn't going on the Must Go Back List.  As a matter of fact.  Never again.
Good food in an attractive and comfortable environment. The noise level allows for conversation; which is a bit rare to find these days.

Valentine's dinner was a ripoff.  Wrong drink was served, and AFTER we got our appetizer. We had to ask for bread. Chocolate sauce with foie gras ? That was not a pleasant combination.  No care in how the plates look whatsoever. They just stack everything in top of each other ( filet mignon on top of asparagus, on top of mashed potatoes.... why!? ).  Dessert was a lie. The lava cake was completely over cooked (no lava to be found) and the vol au vent was a joke.  Not a single time were we asked if everything was alright.  Oh, and it was $87 per person, no drinks included, not even a coffee.  Food was ok to good but boring, service was bad, price was ridiculous.  Dont get me wrong, we are regulars and when you come for their $18 prix fixe for brunch the value is amazing.  But this dinner made both my wife and myself feel we got ripped off, which is not nice for Valentine's Day.  Shame on you benchmark.
Great food, great service, great music, great price!

This restaurant is easy to miss from 5th avenue and one of the better places to eat in Park Slope. The wines are really great and the steaks are pretty tasty too. I do wish they would change their menu up a bit every so often, but the service and food are really good for this area.
This place is amazing!!! I love it even de pudding was spectacular....

Great brunch here. Set.in an old ice House this place is cozy and they have a tent on the patio with heaters in winter to keep you plenty warm if.you choose.  I recommend the Short Rib Benedict, Steak and Eggs and thier Bloody Benchmark a Bloody Mary made with bourbon served with a piece of beef jerky.
Amazing brunch here.  The sausage gravy and biscuits is off the hook.  I came on my bday and they took super good care of me without us even really mentioning it!
My favorite steak house
They have great service and the food is good.
Nice steaks
Awesome place, great service, great food

Awesome spot to kick back and enjoy. Went here on a Wednesday during the day and had a beer and hung out. Felt comfortable and there were some lunchtime folks there for a beer and some quick food. They have a nice outside patio area, too. Great music- 90's grunge and that kinda good stuff. Thumbs up.
very good steak and fancy ambiance. great place to host events too

The scenery here is so simple, yet so beautiful!🍃 It's basically the driveway to the restaurant turned into an outdoor dining experience!🍴 The overhead white tarp glows brilliantly with the stream of white lights.⚘ The greenery adds to its elegant feel.🍀 But be prepared to be one with nature!🐞🕷 Take it all in with delight, as you sip on fine wine🍷 After all, you are outdoors!

I've had brunch and dinner here and both were fabulous. Most of the seating is outside, but they have a tarp to give shade in the summer and heaters in the winter. Not only is the food great, but they give you enough for leftovers. The staff is courteous and the last time I was there we got a free glass of champagne.
Pretty good but burger was overcooked
Amazing restaurant! The service was so great and we got the fillet mignon and scottish salmon which were both phenomenal. Get the chocolate dessert too!

This is a wonderful brunch spot-fresh ingredients, affordable for the quality and delicious dishes. They offer a two course deal; I always choose the grilled strawberry goat cheese salad followed by the crabcake benedict! When I am interested in something sweet, I love getting the pancakes here! You must also try their vanilla lemonade- best lemonade that I've ever tried. For the wine lovers, try the pinot noir blanc - it is a white wine from Germany! Benchmark is great for dinner as well.

Was there this past Saturday. The food was AMAZING. Lobster salad was not only delish,, but plentiful. The Short ribs three ways were probably the best I've had to date. The entrees, Filet and bone in ribeye, were perfectly seasoned, cook and were very tender. The sides, mac and cheese, hand cut fries and brussel sprouts , were also tasty, but the brussel sprouts were a little tough, I prefer a small pasta over the shells they used for the mac and cheeses, but overall, I still have to give this experience 5 stars. Would definitely go back when in Brooklyn again.
Very quiet the menu is great the cocktails awesome
The food is always excellent, the staff wonderful and they have great taste in music!  Great beers & wine too!

Went for my birthday on a cold night in February and had to keep my jacket on the entire time. It was as if there was no heating. The food went cold kind of quickly because of temperature of the room. That considered, the food was really tasty. The steaks were cooked perfectly and the cocktails were delicious!  Is love to see what it's like in the summer, I'm sure the whole experience would be amazing.
Service was good but food is way over rated, steak was so over cooked it was difficult to swallow. Would not recommend.

I dined at Benchmark last night with a friend. When we walked in, we were seated right away. We asked for a bigger table but unfortunately they were unable to accommodate us. A couple of moments after we sat down, a family with young kids were seated next to us. We really wanted a quiet dinner, so we politely asked the manager to seat us an empty table across the room. They were able to do it and menus were brought. The waiter was an absolute pleasure to work with. He was very well versed in the menu and was able to suggest the perfect dishes that would make our night. We ordered the Trio of Short Ribs, Assorted Cheese Plate, Burger and Tuna. We also brought our own wine -- They charge a $30 corking fee. The food was absolutely phenomenal and well priced. They cooked the burger at a perfect medium rare and the tuna at a perfect rare. (Makes me happy because some places just really screw up the temperature). Overall it was a lovely night, great company and great food.
My favorite restaurant in the area great food with an better ambiance.
Benchmark offers delicious cuisine, using fine, fresh ingredients-highly recommend this restaurant!

Mind you i went to this restaurant at least 6 months ago and I'm dying to go back.  The food is simply memorable.   The salad, steaks, seafood, drinks are to die for.  I will definitely recommend this place to all my friends
Amazing steak Peter Luger's or Morton's quality with out the price highly recommend

5 stars all around. 1st: The Food Everything was cooked EXACTLY as requested , some rare others super well done etc. I had the seared sea scallops as an entree, streak as my main, and the cookies and cream egg roll for desert. Everything was perfection.  The steak here was far better than the steak at STK. Without question.  2nd: The Staff Bartosz was delightful along with the rest of the wait staff. No glasses were ever empty, bread basket always remained full.  3rd: The Ambience Beautiful, simply beautiful. Sit outside if weather allows.  4th: Night Spot The cocktails are reasonably priced and my friends said they were good.

Visiting from Kansas City and came here for our Anniversary/ my birthday and it was amazing!!! The food and atmosphere and staff were incredible!!!!! We started with a salad which was very yummy. My husband loved the bread! We each had steak and since were feom KC we love steak. This steak was amazing. I loved the carmalized marrow. BEST BIRTHDAY DINNER EVER!!!

I dined here on a Tuesday evening and opted to sit indoors over the outdoor seating area simply because of the humidity. Both spaces are lovely and in slightly cooler temps, I'd be outside. We started with the Saxelby cheese plate which delicious, save for the blue cheese I'll never eat, along with the foie gras. Both were delicious and plates were definitely cleaned before moving onto the filet mignon entrees. I ordered my steak medium and it was definitely more on the medium-rare side, which was OK. Wonderfully seasoned and delicious despite my request to be prepared with butter or oil.  This is definitely a great place for date night but not too date-sy that you feel uncomfortable if you're not there on a date.The staff was very attentive, helpful and friendly. I'll be returning for the cheeseburger and mac and cheese!

I visited Benchmark with my husband on a random Monday afternoon. Our server was amazing from the start. He was very attentive to our needs and didn't wait to be asked for anything. We started with the cobb salad and lobster bisque which were both delicious. I don't know where they got that bacon but YUM. We also ordered the Sweet Tea with St.Germaine. It was refreshing and strong! Our main courses were the meatloaf and the pressed chicken sandwich which were also delicious. Loved the cozy outdoor atmosphere. Will definitely be back!!

Attractive space, excellent service, super good cocktails, yummy appetizers and perfectly cooked steak. We had two appetizers (seared fois gras and a soup) and split a large ribeye steak. Also had the fries and the charred brussels sprouts with the steak which were delicious!  What more could we ask for? Since it is winter the space is quite small, but the outside courtyard area is large and I look forward to sitting outside once the weather warms up.

We love Benchmark! Been twice, including once for the Thanksgiving prix fixe, which was amazing. Phenomenal steaks, and the prime rib was like nothing I've had before! Great wine too, and lovely atmosphere (love the antique building). A gem that deserves to be better-known!
It was a great spot for a romantic dinner date.  Mellow atmosphere with a wonderful staff.  Food was top notch.  Creative menu and delicious!
Kobe steak + goat cheese mashed potatoes was incredible.
delicious everything. so good
I went for restaurant week and had an amazing meal for an extremely reasonable price.  Can't wait to go back.
Awesome
You'll love the muffins since they are made in house, fresh and warm and delicious with the butter. A good mix of vegetarian and meat options, best for brunch.

This restaurant has amazing character. I visited in July to do a photo shoot and I had the great pleasure of meeting the owner and seeing the place empty.  I appreciated the decor of Benchmark the most!

The cuisine is New American and the setting is casual yet nice enough for a nice date night out. In warmer temps, be sure to sit in their front outside area which has a canvas canopy overhead. Don't miss the marinated steak and tomato salad, which featured baby arugula, spiced goat cheese, and a cilantro pesto. The steak was nicely flavored and thin, which worked well with the goat cheese and the cilantro pesto.
great service and lovely. not great for veggies
steak and home fries are the best!!!

Visited this place for Restaurant Week and want to go again to try more of the full menu. The evening started off with a delicious pea soup with lobster and creme fraiche, very well paired. The halibut in the main course was delicious but the reduction and vegetables accompanying it didn't really make sense. The panna cotta for dessert didn't really have much flavor. The service was great, I could barely put down my water glass after a sip before it was filled again. Some visitors might find this too attentive but as someone who drinks a lot of water it was absolutely perfect. I'm sure once I revisit this place again the three star rating will become four.

Very cute place, weather was perfect for outside seating. It started off very good, excellent appetizers, wine selection is great we got some Rioja, but then a steak took forever to come out at least 45min wait, and it was ok it was not great. Overall it is not a bad place, but probably would not be my first choice for a steak house

We discovered this restaurant by chance, wanting to go to the nearby "La moutarde" which had excellent critics but just disappeared (was sold to a french bakery). Benchmark is an excellent French-style restaurant. The three courses of the menu were all perfect. You should absolutely be placed outside, in the patio, and not inside were the atmosphere is dark, heavy. We met the young chef, not at all a Frenchman but a young american who learned a lot by working with good chefs. Quite sympathetic. Very good place, very good service, good wines at reasonable prices. The service was supervised by a couple of nice women, very attentioned.

I've seen Benchmark before at popups around the city. When I saw their sign, it looked promising. After being turned down by three other Park Slope restaurants, Benchmark will be your savior. Their food is solid and right now they are doing a Restaurant Week promo. Three courses for $38. My favorite was the pork chops and their egg roll cookie dough dessert was unlike anything I've had before. Nice date place.
Small but popular restaurant frequented by hip locals.

I've had fairly mixed experiences here.  Been here at least 8-10 times, and I wouldn't keep coming back if it weren't pretty solid.  It's definitely got good steak, good brunch, good brews at the bar and some other things on the menu have been great too.  I also really like the location - nice decor and a good sized outdoor space.  But there are parts that seem pretty unreliable - e.g. deserts are hit or miss, appetizers are hit or miss, service is hit or miss, wait times are unpredictable, etc.  I wouldn't come here for a special occasion where the expectations are high, but if you come for steak or brunch it's pretty reliable, and if you don't mind taking a gamble it'll surprise you sometimes.
Amazing and surprisingly affordable brunch. A bit difficult to find.
Delicious brunch, excellent drinks and very attentive service.
Awesome spot with great food. Boneless strip steak and cookie dough egg roll are incredible.

It is nice that Park Slope finally has a steakhouse, but don't expect the machismo and edge of a Manhattan beef joint (not a male server in sight). Good rib steak and hash browns, though, and a perfectly acceptable, if pedestrian, wine list. Very nice outdoor area if you like dining al fresco. Otherwise, head midtown for Benson's or The Palm.
1st time there, treat like old time customers. Courtesy matched quality, thank you Billy for a great dinner.
one of the best brunch places in BK
talk about benchmarks! best newcomer in park slope in years. meticulous preparation, fantastic flavors, excellent new space, can't wait for brunch and warm weather to sit on the terrace!

The upside: The food was excellent. We had the Filet Mignon and the 26oz Porterhouse for the entrée - it steak was unbelievable. The Fois Gras appetizer was excellent as well. **If you appreciate a good cut of steak, this is the place. If you like to eat steaks at Applebees, don't waster your time or money. The downside: The service was good, not great and definitely needs improvement. I made reservations earlier in the week and they didn't have it when I arrived. I wasn't thrilled (it was our anniversary) but they gave us a table anyway. It took about ten minutes to take our drink orders and another ten for the drinks to arrive. Besides that hiccup, the service was good for the remainder of the evening. Verdict: Definitely worth going to for the food alone. I'm sure as the restaurant develops they will fix the minor service issues. It's definitely not appropriate for a restaurant of that caliber.
